# Custom Domain for GitHub Pages
# ===============================
# To use a custom domain:
#
# 1. Rename this file to 'CNAME' (remove .example)
# 2. Replace the example domain below with your actual domain
# 3. Configure DNS at your provider:
#    - For apex domain (example.com): Add A records pointing to GitHub's IPs
#    - For subdomain (app.example.com): Add CNAME record pointing to <username>.github.io
#
# GitHub's current IP addresses for A records:
#   185.199.108.153
#   185.199.109.153
#   185.199.110.153
#   185.199.111.153
#
# 4. Commit and push this file
# 5. The build will automatically use '/' as base path instead of '/StoryCraft-Studio/'
#
# Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/pages/configuring-a-custom-domain-for-your-github-pages-site

storycraft.example.com
